Hi @Alanthur, Thanks for creating the issue. 

Default policy.json is equivalent to https://src.fedoraproject.org/rpms/containers-common/raw/main/f/default-policy.json

If you don't want any default registries configured feel free to use this one
```json
{
    "default": [
        {
            "type": "insecureAcceptAnything"
        }
    ],
    "transports":
        {
            "docker-daemon":
                {
                    "": [{"type":"insecureAcceptAnything"}]
                }
        }
}
```

If you want to read more about how to configure `policy.json` for a fine grained control then you can follow the man-page here: https://github.com/containers/image/blob/main/docs/containers-policy.json.5.md

Thanks

